  "text": "I might make the analogy then in that when a polarization in the atmosphere occurs to create thunderstorms, lightning, and much activity. This more vivid experience could be likened to the polarization in consciousness which creates the more vivid experience. Would this be appropriate? I am wrong. There is a shallowness to this analogy in that one entity's attention might be focused upon a storm for the duration of the storm. However, the storm a producing conditions are not constant, whereas the polarizing conditions are constant. Given this disclaimer, we may agree with your analogy.",
